        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 6:20AM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 619 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers near
Lewiston Woodville, or 15 miles northwest of Williamston, moving
north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of east central
Halifax County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Doppler radar has indicated weak rotation with this shower. If the
rotation strengthens, a warning may need to be issued.</instruction>
